args: Goodness, but that is a dense tome!
It seems I have underestimated how\nsmart and clever you are.
You certainly are! Now then, might you\ntell me more about this book of yours?
Hey there, Linnea! Doing a little\nweapon maintenance today?
I saw you sharpening this selfsame blade\nyesterday as well. Admirably prudent.
Dad always said that regular\nmaintenance was important.
It's great that you took his\ninstructions to heart like that.
It's not COMING from anywhere!\nIt's always BEEN like this!
You people are all so...so NICE, and it\nmakes it impossible for me to hate you!
All I want is to hate humans...
See, that doesn't make sense to me.\nWeren't you raised by humans?
Do you actually want to hate your parents?
My mom and dad are the ones\nI want to hate most.
I just...I love them so much...\nand I wish I could hate them instead.
Dad died first, then Mom a few years later.
They both went peacefully...\nAnd on both of those days, it was raining...
Downpours heavy enough to drown out\neven the sound of my tears.
I've known nothing but sadness\never since they left me.
The sadness... The rain... My loneliness...\nNone of it ever ends.
They got old, and I was left behind.
I can see how painful these memories\nare for you, but let me say one thing...

I didn't say not to—I said you CAN'T.
Even if we showed you the ugliest
side of the worst human in the world,
you still wouldn't be able to do it.
But that's all I have.\nIt's all I've been striving for.
I'm sad and alone and I want to forget,\nso why can't I hate them?!

Because no amount of bad behavior on
the part of random humans can make you
forget all the wonderful things you love
about your own parents.
Your parents loved you—a REAL kind of\nlove—and that isn't something you can\njust forget about or wish away.
And I think you know that.
It doesn't matter that you're sylvan and\nthey're human—you had a bond.
It's all right to remember them, Linnea,\nand it's all right for that to hurt.
You can still live a happy life and\nremember the people you've lost.
I don't... I don't understand that.\nAnd if I DID come to understand it...
No! Remembering is sad! It's lonely!\nI don't WANT to be alone!
Oh, poor Linnea. I know it's difficult,\nand I know you did your best.
But you are no longer alone.
({player_name} is with me...\nElisanne is holding me...)
(I...can't hate them...\nJust like I couldn't back then...)
